XSLT (Extensible Stylesheet Language Transformations) = used to transform the contents of an XML document into another document format.


- An XLT is itself an XML document with elements, attributes and processing instructions from the XSLT vocabulary.



How to convert XML to XSLT

- Translate a source document into a result document.

- To perform this translation, you need an XSLT processor.



Attaching an XSLT Style Sheet: 

- The syntax of the processing instruction:
<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xml" href="url" ?>



Applying a Template

- To apply a template: 
<xsl:apply-templates select="expression" />
